00:47.756 --> 00:48.631
- AH!

00:48.715 --> 00:51.384
NOW, THESE ARE THE MOMENTS
I LIVE FOR.

00:51.468 --> 00:54.137
B AND DOG,
OUT ON A MORNING STROLL.

00:54.220 --> 00:55.638
- [barks]

00:55.722 --> 00:57.849
- HOME STRETCH, HAPS.

00:57.932 --> 01:01.019
SHALL WE?

01:01.102 --> 01:02.228
- TALLY HO!

01:02.312 --> 01:03.980
- TALLY HO, INDEED.

01:05.063 --> 01:07.567
[laughing]

01:08.943 --> 01:10.403
ONWARD!

01:10.487 --> 01:11.529
[engine roaring]

01:11.613 --> 01:13.490
[paws screeching]

01:16.159 --> 01:18.495
AN ATHLETE AND A GENTLEMAN.

01:18.578 --> 01:20.038
I'M IMPRESSED,
MR. HIGGENBOTTOM.

01:21.998 --> 01:25.251
HEY, GALS, DO I HAVE
AN ANECDOTE FOR YOU.

01:25.335 --> 01:26.753
SO I'M AT THE ARMY SURPLUS,

01:26.836 --> 01:28.338
TREATING MYSELF
TO A NEW HOT PLATE, WHEN--

01:28.421 --> 01:30.799
girls: AW!

01:30.882 --> 01:32.467
- WHAT'S GOING ON, YOU GUYS?

01:32.550 --> 01:34.511
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN
ON THE WORLD WIDE WEB?

01:34.594 --> 01:37.680
[laughing hysterically]

01:37.764 --> 01:38.973
- HUH?

01:39.057 --> 01:40.558
- WHAT?

01:40.642 --> 01:41.851
WHAT?

01:41.935 --> 01:43.561
- SO CUTE.

01:43.645 --> 01:44.312
- I WANT ONE.

01:44.395 --> 01:46.523
I'M TEXTING MY MOM RIGHT NOW.

01:46.606 --> 01:48.733
- I LOVE THEM SO MUCH.

01:49.818 --> 01:53.404
- OH, OH!
HE'S DOING IT AGAIN!

01:53.488 --> 01:54.906
- OH, I LOVE IT
WHEN HE DOES THAT.

01:54.989 --> 01:58.368
- PLEASE, SOMEBODY TELL ME
WHAT IT IS.

01:58.451 --> 01:59.536
- PUPPY NET!

01:59.619 --> 02:01.913
- HUH?

02:01.996 --> 02:04.082
- FIVE PUPPIES, SIX WEEKS OLD,

02:04.165 --> 02:06.251
ON A LIVE WEBCAM 24/7.

02:06.334 --> 02:07.585
- [gasps]

02:07.669 --> 02:08.336
- SOME LUCKY DORK OWNS THEM.

02:08.419 --> 02:10.295
- OOH!

02:10.380 --> 02:12.257
LET ME AT IT!

02:12.340 --> 02:14.133
COME ON, LET ME AT IT!

02:14.217 --> 02:16.219
LET...ME...AT IT!

02:16.302 --> 02:18.805
all: [disappointedly] AW!

02:18.888 --> 02:19.806
- GIMME!

02:19.889 --> 02:22.225
WHA--PUPPIES.

02:22.308 --> 02:23.393
PUPPIES.
WHERE ARE THE PUPPIES?

02:23.476 --> 02:25.895
- [sighs]

02:25.979 --> 02:27.313
SNACK TIME.

02:27.397 --> 02:29.107
- WELL, WHEN ARE THEY
COMING BACK?

02:29.190 --> 02:32.277
- [sighs] YOU KINDA
JUST GOT TO BE THERE.

02:34.487 --> 02:35.905
- [speaking]

02:35.989 --> 02:37.574
- GIVE ME A SEC, BOY.

02:37.657 --> 02:39.742
I JUST NEED TO SEE
THEIR SOFT LITTLE BELLIES

02:39.826 --> 02:41.995
AND THEIR SOFT, SOFT BABY FUR

02:42.078 --> 02:45.582
AND THEIR SOFT, SOFT, SOFT
FLOPPY EARS.

02:49.752 --> 02:52.797
MMM, YOU'RE LUCKY, HAPPY.

02:52.881 --> 02:55.133
BEEFY GOODNESS,
NOW WITH 25% BEEF,

02:55.216 --> 02:56.342
COMING RIGHT UP.

02:56.426 --> 02:58.219
- [speaks excitedly]

02:58.303 --> 02:59.512
[pants]

02:59.596 --> 03:00.471
- [sighs]
I WONDER WHAT PUPPIES EAT.

03:00.555 --> 03:02.849
WHATEVER IT IS,
I BET IT'S REALLY CUTE.

03:04.267 --> 03:06.102
OH, I JUST CAN'T STOP THINKING
ABOUT THEM.

03:06.185 --> 03:07.770
[puppies barking]

03:07.854 --> 03:11.107
- I DIDN'T KNOW ANY LIVING
CREATURE COULD BE THIS CUTE!

03:11.190 --> 03:13.109
THANK YOU, PUPPY NET!

03:13.192 --> 03:14.569
- BEN.

03:14.652 --> 03:17.405
- [Happy whining]

03:18.948 --> 03:20.783
- I CALL THAT ONE MR. CHUB.

03:20.867 --> 03:23.661
HE'S MY FAVORITE.

03:23.745 --> 03:25.121
crash!

03:25.204 --> 03:27.123
- SHOW ME THE PUPPIES!

03:27.206 --> 03:28.458
AGAIN?

03:28.541 --> 03:29.375
WHERE DO THEY NEED TO GO
SO BAD?

03:29.459 --> 03:31.461
WHAT, THEY'RE GOING
TO THE RACETRACK?

03:31.544 --> 03:32.670
THEY GOT A HOT TIP ON A HORSE?

03:32.754 --> 03:33.504
OH, BOY.

03:33.588 --> 03:35.632
- WELL, THEY HAVE TO TAKE
BREAKS.

03:35.715 --> 03:37.425
IT'S EXHAUSTING BEING THAT CUTE.

03:37.508 --> 03:40.470
ANYWAY, WHEN YOU DO SEE THEM,
IT'LL CHANGE YOUR LIFE.

03:40.553 --> 03:43.806
I'M PRETTY SURE THEIR EARS
ARE MADE OF VELVET.

03:43.890 --> 03:45.892
AND THEIR PAWS, OH, THEIR PAWS.

03:45.975 --> 03:48.144
- STOP, STOP, STOP!

03:48.227 --> 03:49.187
NO SPOILERS.

03:49.270 --> 03:50.146
[clears throat]

03:50.229 --> 03:51.105
THIS IS MY PRIVATE NUMBER.

03:51.189 --> 03:53.441
CALL ME
THE SECOND THEY GET BACK.

03:53.524 --> 03:55.485
I'LL MAKE IT WORTH YOUR WHILE.

03:55.568 --> 03:57.862
MR. PANTS' TOO.

03:59.781 --> 04:02.367
LOUSY PUPPIES, ALWAYS ON BREAK.

04:02.450 --> 04:04.285
IF YOU'RE GOING TO DO
A LIVE SHOW, DO A LIVE SHOW.

04:04.369 --> 04:07.497
YOU JUST CAN'T GO BACKSTAGE
EVERY FIVE MINUTES.

04:09.499 --> 04:12.710
WITH THAT WORK ETHIC, YOU'LL
NEVER MAKE IT TO BROADWAY.

04:12.794 --> 04:14.295
[bell rings]

04:18.675 --> 04:20.301
HELLO?

04:20.385 --> 04:21.678
HIGGENBOTTOM PICKING UP.

04:21.761 --> 04:23.930
FOUR HONEYBEE UNIFORMS,
LIGHT STARCH.

04:24.013 --> 04:25.181
- [speaks indignantly]

04:25.264 --> 04:28.101
- SORRY.
AND ONE VELOUR TRACKSUIT.

04:28.184 --> 04:30.186
HELLO?
HELLO?

04:30.269 --> 04:31.688
DING, DING, DING, DING.
HELLO!

04:31.771 --> 04:33.189
RING, RING, RING.
HELLO, HELLO!

04:33.272 --> 04:36.359
- I HAVE NEVER SEEN ANYTHING
SO SWEET.

04:36.442 --> 04:38.653
- OH, IT DOESN'T GET
ANY CUTER.

04:38.736 --> 04:40.780
- LOOK, HE'S CHEWING
HIS SISTER'S EAR AGAIN.

04:40.863 --> 04:41.864
AHN, AHN, AHN!

04:44.283 --> 04:46.369
- [coughs]

04:46.452 --> 04:48.162
- I WANT TO SEE!
I WANT TO SEE!

04:49.455 --> 04:51.541
SOFT, YOUNG, NOT OLD.

04:51.624 --> 04:55.795
[people exclaiming]

05:00.466 --> 05:03.219
- PUPPIES!

05:03.302 --> 05:04.929
OH, COME ON!

05:05.013 --> 05:06.639
REALLY?

05:06.723 --> 05:07.223
UGH!
REALLY?

05:07.306 --> 05:09.267
- LOOK AT THAT PUPPY!

05:09.350 --> 05:10.852
IT'S A PUPPY.

05:10.935 --> 05:11.853
- ...CUTEST THINGS,
AREN'T THEY?

05:11.936 --> 05:16.524
- EVERYONE ELSE CAN SEE THEM.
WHY CAN'T I?

05:16.607 --> 05:19.652
I MEAN, I'M A GOOD PERSON,
RIGHT?

05:19.736 --> 05:22.280
I RECYCLE.

05:22.363 --> 05:23.531
I VOLUNTEER.

05:23.614 --> 05:25.575
I GIVE FAMILY MEMBERS
A DISCOUNT ON TAFFY.

05:25.658 --> 05:26.743
AM I RIGHT, BOY?

05:26.826 --> 05:29.078
- [grumbles]

05:29.162 --> 05:31.998
- AW!
LOOK AT THAT.

05:36.711 --> 05:39.547
UGH!

05:39.630 --> 05:41.924
- CHECK OUT THE PUPPY PILE.

05:42.008 --> 05:43.134
AW!

05:43.217 --> 05:45.887
I LOVE IT WHEN THEY DO THAT.

05:51.309 --> 05:53.394
- I HAVE A JUNIOR POLICEMAN'S
BADGE; LET ME IN.

05:53.478 --> 05:54.937
- CALLING ALL CARS!
CALLING ALL CARS!

05:55.021 --> 05:56.981
409 AT THE WHARF.
SEA LION UNDER THE INFLUENCE.

05:57.065 --> 05:59.650
[siren wailing]

05:59.734 --> 06:01.819
- WAIT!

06:01.903 --> 06:03.446
[panting]

06:03.529 --> 06:04.781
[puppies barking]

06:04.864 --> 06:05.907
- AW, WOULD YA--

06:05.990 --> 06:08.409
THOSE PUPPIES, THEY REMIND YOU
WHAT REALLY MATTERS.

06:08.493 --> 06:08.951
vroom!

06:09.035 --> 06:10.787
[feet screeching]

06:10.870 --> 06:13.748
- I KNOW.

06:15.083 --> 06:16.125
- GOT IT!

06:16.209 --> 06:17.293
- HEY, PUPPY LOVERS.

06:17.376 --> 06:19.462
THE PUPPIES HAVE A VISIT
WITH THE VET TODAY.

06:19.545 --> 06:20.588
CHECK BACK LATER.

06:20.671 --> 06:21.964
[laughs]

06:22.048 --> 06:25.551
- AW, GOING TO THE VET.

06:25.635 --> 06:27.929
- THEY'RE SO CUTE!

06:30.765 --> 06:33.476
- [yells]

06:33.559 --> 06:33.810
FRUSTRATED!

06:33.893 --> 06:34.602
- HEY!

06:37.647 --> 06:39.440
- THE PUPPIES HAVE A VISIT
WITH THE VET TODAY.

06:39.524 --> 06:39.774
CHECK BACK LATER.

06:39.857 --> 06:42.568
[laughs]

06:42.652 --> 06:43.486
- [growls unhappily]

06:46.405 --> 06:48.157
[crickets chirping]

06:48.241 --> 06:51.244
[poignant string music]

06:51.327 --> 06:59.127
♪ ♪

07:02.296 --> 07:05.133
- I CLEARED MY SCHEDULE,
PUPPIES.

07:05.216 --> 07:06.509
I CAN WAIT FOR DAYS.

07:06.592 --> 07:07.885
- [barking excitedly]

07:11.472 --> 07:12.849
- [sighs]
OH, HAPPY.

07:12.932 --> 07:14.350
WHEN YOU ROLL
AROUND THE FLOOR LIKE THAT,

07:14.433 --> 07:16.060
IT LEAVES A SMEAR.

07:22.316 --> 07:24.360
[puppies barking]

07:24.443 --> 07:25.862
[gasps]
THEY'RE BACK!

07:25.945 --> 07:28.114
BU-BUFFERING?

07:28.197 --> 07:30.825
UGH! WHY DO I PAY
FOR HIGH-SPEED INTERNET?

07:37.373 --> 07:39.542
ACHOO!
[puppies bark]

07:44.797 --> 07:47.091
[puppies bark]
HUH?

07:48.384 --> 07:49.677
[puppies bark]

07:52.096 --> 07:53.764
[yawns]
[puppies bark]

07:55.558 --> 08:00.146
[puppies barking intermittently]

08:04.317 --> 08:05.693
[puppies bark]
[Mighty B laughs]

08:09.906 --> 08:11.407
[puppies bark]

08:14.994 --> 08:17.288
ARGH!

08:20.333 --> 08:22.710
GO FAST. GO FAST.
GO FAST. GO FASTER.

08:22.793 --> 08:24.212
FASTER, FASTER, FASTER,
FASTER, FAST--

08:24.295 --> 08:26.255
GO FAST!

08:26.339 --> 08:26.631
[electricity crackling]

08:31.135 --> 08:34.472
OH, MAN, DO I NEED THIS.

08:34.554 --> 08:35.389
IT'S JUST NOT MEANT TO BE.

08:35.472 --> 08:37.433
THE UNIVERSE HAS
PERFECTLY GOOD REASONS

08:37.515 --> 08:40.561
IT DOESN'T WANT ME TO SEE
THOSE PUPPIES, RIGHT?

08:40.645 --> 08:43.438
I MEAN, IF WE SHARE ONE MOMENT
OF HAPPINESS TOGETHER,

08:43.522 --> 08:46.359
APPARENTLY THE LAWS OF PHYSICS
WILL CEASE TO APPLY

08:46.442 --> 08:48.402
AND THE TIME-SPACE CONTINUUM
WILL COLLAPSE.

08:48.486 --> 08:48.986
THANKS, UNIVERSE!

08:49.070 --> 08:50.947
THANKS SO MUCH.

08:51.030 --> 08:52.949
- THANKS FOR THE STEAK BONES.

08:53.032 --> 08:55.451
MY FIVE PUPPIES
WILL REALLY LOVE THESE.

08:55.534 --> 08:58.246
[laughs annoyingly]

09:06.379 --> 09:09.090
- HAPPY, WHERE YOU GOING?

09:10.591 --> 09:11.300
[gasps]

09:11.384 --> 09:15.137
WHO COULD HATE PUPPIES SO MUCH?

09:15.221 --> 09:17.431
- [barking angrily]

09:17.515 --> 09:21.477
- OH, HAPPY,
YOU DON'T HATE PUPPIES.

09:21.560 --> 09:25.648
OH, HAPPY,
MY POOR MIDDLE-AGED DOG.

09:25.731 --> 09:26.983
NATURALLY, YOU FEEL INADEQUATE

09:27.066 --> 09:28.192
IN THE PRESENCE
OF SOFT, ADORABLE PUPPIES.

09:28.276 --> 09:30.945
ALL THE PET BOOKS COVER THIS.

09:31.028 --> 09:32.196
HOW COULD I HAVE BEEN SO BLIND?

09:32.280 --> 09:34.991
HAPPY!

09:35.074 --> 09:35.700
[bell rings]

09:43.332 --> 09:45.960
[panting]

09:55.469 --> 09:57.680
- [coughing hoarsely]

09:58.931 --> 10:00.433
- HEY, BOY, YOU NEED SOME WATER.

10:00.516 --> 10:03.227
YOU BETTER COME IN
AND LIE DOWN.

10:04.061 --> 10:06.063
- HEY!

10:06.147 --> 10:07.106
- BE RIGHT BACK.

10:07.189 --> 10:09.692
[water running]

10:09.775 --> 10:12.987
- [sniffing]

10:13.070 --> 10:14.864
[growls]

10:19.201 --> 10:20.703
[puppy barks]

10:23.956 --> 10:25.499
[knocking]

10:26.083 --> 10:28.711
- HELLO?

10:28.794 --> 10:30.129
HUH.

10:31.047 --> 10:33.966
- HAPPY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN THERE?

10:41.640 --> 10:43.809
HAPPY!

10:43.893 --> 10:44.143
[suspenseful music]

10:44.226 --> 10:47.104
- HMM?

10:53.194 --> 10:55.863
- HAPPY, NO!

10:55.946 --> 10:57.490
YOU'LL DO HARD TIME
IN THE POUND!

11:02.328 --> 11:04.497
OH!

11:04.580 --> 11:12.463
♪ ♪

11:17.176 --> 11:19.261
[tails thumping]

11:21.389 --> 11:24.600
- AW, PUPPIES AND HAPPY!

11:24.683 --> 11:27.937
AND THEY SAID
IT COULDN'T GET ANY CUTER.

11:28.020 --> 11:28.854
THEY WERE WRONG!

11:45.871 --> 11:48.958
- HI, BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,
DO SOLEMNLY SWEAR

11:49.041 --> 11:50.543
THAT I WILL FAITHFULLY EXECUTE
THE OFFICE

11:50.626 --> 11:53.629
OF PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES.

11:53.712 --> 11:55.631
AH!

11:55.714 --> 11:57.383
- [growling]

11:57.466 --> 11:58.676
- SORRY, HAPS.

11:58.759 --> 12:00.928
I GOT LOST IN A CATEGORY FIVE
BRAINSTORM.

12:01.011 --> 12:01.512
ELECTION DAY
IS ONLY A WEEK AWAY,

12:01.595 --> 12:03.639
AND I STILL CAN'T DECIDE

12:03.722 --> 12:05.724
HOW I WANT TO EARN
MY DEMOCRACY BADGE.

12:09.228 --> 12:11.021
I MEAN, PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES

12:11.105 --> 12:12.523
WOULD BE THE OBVIOUS CHOICE,

12:12.606 --> 12:13.983
BUT I CAN'T UPROOT OUR FAMILY
TO WASHINGTON.

12:14.066 --> 12:15.943
HMM.

12:16.026 --> 12:17.945
OH, I DO OWN THAT NICE GAVEL.

12:18.028 --> 12:21.949
MAYBE I'LL BE A JUDGE OR
A MAGISTRATE OR A BAILIFF OR--

12:22.032 --> 12:22.616
OOH, THERE SHOULD BE
SOME OPENINGS

12:22.700 --> 12:23.909
ON THE SUPREME COURT SOON.

12:23.993 --> 12:27.329
THEN AGAIN, AMERICA CAN
ALWAYS USE MORE COMPTROLLERS.

12:27.413 --> 12:28.330
[both gasp]

12:28.414 --> 12:30.916
[dog barking]

12:31.000 --> 12:33.836
[dog chomping]

12:38.883 --> 12:42.678
THESE DOGS ARE ACTING
LIKE ANIMALS.

12:42.761 --> 12:44.180
THIS IS CHAOS.
THIS IS ANARCHY.

12:44.263 --> 12:46.223
THIS IS...

12:46.307 --> 12:47.516
AN OPPORTUNITY!

12:47.600 --> 12:50.519
I'M GOING TO RUN FOR DOGCATCHER.

12:50.603 --> 12:51.270
- [speaks inquisitively]

12:51.353 --> 12:53.856
- YEAH, DOGCATCHER.

12:53.939 --> 12:57.526
YOU KNOW, THE CITY EMPLOYEE
WHO HUNTS DOWN DIRTY STRAYS.

12:57.610 --> 12:58.486
- [muttering]

12:58.569 --> 13:00.571
- SOUNDS LIKE A RESPECTABLE WAY

13:00.654 --> 13:02.490
TO EARN MY DEMOCRACY BADGE,
RIGHT?

13:02.573 --> 13:04.366
- [barking vehemently]

13:04.450 --> 13:08.037
- NOW, SEE, HAPPY, THAT'S JUST
YOUR CYNICISM TALKING.

13:08.120 --> 13:10.664
NOT ALL DOGCATCHERS
ARE ANTI-DOG.

13:10.748 --> 13:13.501
MOST ARE JUST PRO-CATCHING.

13:13.584 --> 13:14.877
- [growls]

13:14.960 --> 13:16.212
- HEY, I KNOW;

13:16.295 --> 13:18.631
YOU CAN BE MY CAMPAIGN'S
TOP CANINE CONSULTANT.

13:18.714 --> 13:21.175
COME ON; HELP ME WIN
THE DOG VOTE.

13:21.258 --> 13:22.885
I MEAN, WHAT'S THE CURRENT
DOGCATCHER EVER DONE

13:22.968 --> 13:24.345
FOR YOUR SPECIES?

13:24.428 --> 13:27.014
[pounding]

13:27.097 --> 13:29.099
[lilting music]

13:29.183 --> 13:33.938
♪ ♪

13:39.360 --> 13:41.111
[ominous music]

13:41.195 --> 13:42.738
HAL?

13:42.821 --> 13:46.033
HAL THE ICE CREAM MAN
IS ALSO HAL THE DOGCATCHER?

13:46.116 --> 13:47.201
IS THAT EVEN SANITARY?

13:47.284 --> 13:51.288
- ALL RIGHT, I GOT FIVE
ANGRY CALLS ABOUT YOU MUTTS.

13:51.372 --> 13:53.123
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

13:53.207 --> 13:54.833
MY BRIBE PRICE JUST DOUBLED.

13:54.917 --> 13:57.920
NOW IT'S FOUR STRIPS OF BACON
EACH.

14:01.048 --> 14:01.966
- [gasps]

14:02.049 --> 14:04.885
HE'S TRADING JUSTICE FOR BACON?

14:04.969 --> 14:06.637
- [slurps]

14:06.720 --> 14:08.847
- NO WONDER YOU HAVE NO RESPECT
FOR THE OFFICE, HAPS.

14:08.931 --> 14:13.269
DOGS, LEND ME
YOUR SUPER-SENSITIVE EARS.

14:13.352 --> 14:17.231
YOU DON'T HAVE TO HAND OVER
YOUR HARD-EARNED BACON ANYMORE.

14:17.314 --> 14:18.357
VOTE FOR ME,
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,

14:18.440 --> 14:21.110
FOR CITY DOGCATCHER,

14:21.193 --> 14:25.281
AND I PROMISE TO RETURN HONESTY
AND ACTUAL DOG CATCHING

14:25.364 --> 14:27.491
TO THE POST OF DOGCATCHER.

14:33.831 --> 14:37.585
- LOOK, KID, THE DOGS AND I,
WE GOT A GOOD THING GOING.

14:37.668 --> 14:40.462
I GET MY BACON.
THEY STAY OUT OF THE SLAMMER.

14:40.546 --> 14:41.964
SO HOW'S ABOUT YOU RUN ALONG?

14:42.047 --> 14:44.383
FORGET ABOUT POLITICS.

14:44.466 --> 14:46.760
- SIR, I AM NOT FOR SALE.

14:46.844 --> 14:49.847
AND NEITHER IS
MY SENIOR ADVISOR, HAPPY.

14:49.930 --> 14:50.931
LET'S GO, HAPS.
WE HAVE AN ELECTION TO WIN.

14:54.435 --> 14:56.478
[patriotic music]

14:56.562 --> 14:59.273
SOME DOGCATCHERS ONLY CARE
ABOUT HUMANS.

14:59.356 --> 15:01.650
OTHERS ONLY CARE ABOUT DOGS.

15:01.734 --> 15:05.988
BUT I CARE ABOUT EVERYONE--

15:06.071 --> 15:07.448
EVEN YOU, DIRTY WEASELS.

15:10.159 --> 15:11.994
HEAR MY PROMISE.

15:12.077 --> 15:13.495
NO PUPPY LEFT BEHIND!

15:13.579 --> 15:16.332
NOT ON MY WATCH.

15:16.415 --> 15:19.209
THE WORD "DOGCATCHER" SOUNDS
SO NEGATIVE.

15:19.293 --> 15:21.003
I WANT TO BE
YOUR CANINE ADVOCATE.

15:21.086 --> 15:26.008
- [laughs]

15:26.091 --> 15:27.009
- I'M NOT DOING THIS FOR ME.

15:27.092 --> 15:30.929
I'M DOING THIS FOR ROVER
OVER ON LOMBARD STREET

15:31.013 --> 15:33.557
AND FOR FLUFFY
DOWN ON THE CASTRO

15:33.641 --> 15:37.227
AND FOR ALL THE DOGS
IN THE GARBAGE EATERS LOCAL 219.

15:38.937 --> 15:41.440
KEEP DIVING
INTO THE DUMPSTERS, BOYS!

15:42.900 --> 15:47.404
MY FELLOW MAMMALS,
VOTE FOR CHANGE.

15:47.488 --> 15:47.946
VOTE FOR HIGGENBOTTOM!

15:55.454 --> 15:58.374
- MISS HIGGENBOTTOM, YOUR
OPPONENT SAYS YOU HATE DOGS.

15:58.457 --> 15:59.375
IS THIS TRUE?

15:59.458 --> 16:01.043
- HA! RIDICULOUS.

16:01.126 --> 16:03.253
MY BEST FRIEND IS A DOG.

16:05.130 --> 16:08.801
HAPPY, DON'T YOU EMBARRASS ME
IN FRONT OF THE MEDIA ELITE.

16:08.884 --> 16:10.177
HEY, COME ON, BOY!

16:10.260 --> 16:12.513
LET'S SHOW OFF OUR SECRET
BEST FRIENDS HANDSHAKE.

16:12.596 --> 16:13.889
- [speaking quietly]

16:13.972 --> 16:14.765
- I'M EMBARRASSING YOU?

16:14.848 --> 16:18.519
WE WILL DISCUSS THIS LATER.

16:26.276 --> 16:27.569
- BESSIE!
- BESSIE, MISS HIGGENBOTTOM!

16:27.653 --> 16:30.572
[all clamoring]

16:30.656 --> 16:31.573
- OKAY, WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

16:31.657 --> 16:34.576
- [speaking casually]

16:34.660 --> 16:36.453
- YOU KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

16:36.537 --> 16:38.831
WHY CAN'T YOU SUPPORT
MY POLITICAL CAREER?

16:38.914 --> 16:41.208
HAVEN'T I ALWAYS SUPPORTED
YOUR DREAMS AND ASPIRATIONS?

16:41.291 --> 16:44.586
WHO DO YOU THINK PAID FOR
THOSE ARGENTINE TANGO CLASSES?

16:44.670 --> 16:46.880
- [speaking vehemently]

16:46.964 --> 16:49.925
- IT IS NOT CORNY!
IT'S PATRIOTIC.

16:50.008 --> 16:51.552
- [speaking mockingly]

16:51.635 --> 16:53.595
- UH, BESSIE?

16:53.679 --> 16:56.014
THE LATEST POLLS ARE IN.

16:56.098 --> 16:58.350
- HOLD ON, HAPS.
I NEED TO TAKE THIS.

16:58.434 --> 17:00.018
TALK TO ME, PEN.

17:00.102 --> 17:01.770
- ACCORDING
TO THE NUMBER MACHINE,

17:01.854 --> 17:04.897
YOU'VE GOT THE CAT VOTE
AND SOCCER MOMS.

17:04.982 --> 17:06.442
- AND DOGS?

17:06.525 --> 17:07.818
- UH...

17:07.901 --> 17:09.653
THE CATS LOVE YOU.

17:09.737 --> 17:11.613
UH, OKAY.

17:11.696 --> 17:16.785
SO HAL'S STILL GOT THE STRAYS,
SHEPHERDS, LABS, TERRIERS,

17:16.868 --> 17:19.538
TIBETAN WATER DOGS,
WEREWOLVES.

17:19.621 --> 17:21.665
- [barking angrily]

17:21.749 --> 17:24.792
- [gasps]

17:24.877 --> 17:27.296
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
I DON'T HAVE YOUR VOTE?

17:28.172 --> 17:31.133
WE MAY NEED
TO HIRE ME A PROP DOG.

17:37.598 --> 17:40.142
OH, HI, HAL.

17:40.225 --> 17:43.228
SHOULDN'T YOU BE HOME, PREPARING
FOR OUR BIG DEBATE TOMORROW?

17:43.312 --> 17:45.481
- I ONLY CAME BY
TO GIVE YOU A PREVIEW

17:45.564 --> 17:46.607
OF MY NEW ATTACK AD,
THE ONE THAT WILL...

17:46.690 --> 17:49.318
DESTROY YOU!

17:49.401 --> 17:52.446
{\an5}[on recording]
BESSIE SAYS
SHE WANTS TO CATCH DOGS.

17:52.529 --> 17:55.157
BUT THE ONLY THING
WE'VE SEEN HER CATCHING

17:55.240 --> 17:56.617
IS BOOGERS.

17:56.700 --> 17:58.535
TOO BAD THE JOB TITLE
ISN'T "BOOGER CATCHER."

17:58.619 --> 18:00.996
HEY, BESSIE?

18:01.079 --> 18:02.414
HAL'S ATTACK AD
PAID FOR BY HAL.

18:02.498 --> 18:05.542
SO YOU GONNA DROP OUT OF
THE RACE?

18:05.626 --> 18:07.044
- HAL, BUBBALA,

18:07.127 --> 18:07.878
I APPRECIATE YOUR PASSION.

18:07.961 --> 18:10.672
POLITICS NEEDS
PASSIONATE PEOPLE.

18:10.756 --> 18:13.717
BUT VOTERS CARE ABOUT CHANGE,
NOT BOOGERS.

18:14.426 --> 18:17.846
- OOH!

18:17.930 --> 18:20.432
HA!

18:20.516 --> 18:24.520
[melancholy music]

18:24.603 --> 18:26.438
- ANOTHER ROUND
FOR MY FRIEND HERE.

18:26.522 --> 18:27.231
- HUH?

18:30.984 --> 18:32.861
- WHAT DO I WANT?

18:32.945 --> 18:34.363
SAME THING YOU WANT:

18:34.446 --> 18:37.991
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM OUT OF
THIS DOGCATCHER RACE.

18:38.075 --> 18:40.035
COME ON;
GIVE ME SOME DIRT ON HER.

18:40.118 --> 18:43.705
AREN'T YOU TIRED OF BEING
A KEPT DOG?

18:43.789 --> 18:45.374
"HAPPY, SIT."

18:45.457 --> 18:49.294
[imitating Mighty B
unintelligibly]

18:49.378 --> 18:52.840
JOIN ME, AND YOU'LL BE A HERO
TO EVERY DOG IN THIS CITY.

18:52.923 --> 18:56.343
- [speaking uncertainly]

18:56.426 --> 18:58.971
- ARE YOU SURE
YOU CAN'T HELP ME?

18:59.054 --> 19:02.224
NOT EVEN FOR...

19:02.307 --> 19:04.268
BACON-WRAPPED BACON?

19:09.648 --> 19:13.694
ALL YOURS AS SOON AS YOU GIVE ME
SOME DIRT ON BESSIE.

19:13.777 --> 19:16.363
[ominous music]

19:18.156 --> 19:20.993
- SO DEBATE TIME.

19:21.076 --> 19:21.952
IT ALL COMES DOWN
TO THIS MOMENT.

19:22.035 --> 19:23.745
WE'RE NECK AND NECK,
AS THEY SAY.

19:23.829 --> 19:26.915
HUH.
NO NOTECARDS?

19:26.999 --> 19:27.624
NO PREPARATION OF ANY KIND?

19:27.708 --> 19:30.043
HUH, IMPRESSIVE.

19:30.127 --> 19:31.545
- OH, IT WILL BE IMPRESSIVE.

19:31.628 --> 19:35.883
[laughs evilly]

19:41.847 --> 19:43.974
- GREETINGS, CITIZENS.

19:44.057 --> 19:48.687
THE FIRST QUESTION GOES
TO MR. THE ICE CREAM MAN.

19:48.770 --> 19:51.356
HOW MANY DOGS
WOULD A DOGCATCHER CATCH

19:51.440 --> 19:54.484
IF A DOGCATCHER COULD
CATCH DOGS?

19:54.568 --> 19:56.778
AND GO!

19:56.862 --> 19:59.615
- ACTUALLY, I'VE GOT A QUESTION
OF MY OWN.

19:59.698 --> 20:03.368
TELL ME, VOTERS, HOW CAN BESSIE
RUN FOR DOGCATCHER

20:03.452 --> 20:08.290
WHEN SHE'S BREAKING THE LAW
BY WALKING HER OWN DOG...

20:08.373 --> 20:11.877
OFF LEASH?

20:11.960 --> 20:15.213
- THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT--
[screams]

20:17.591 --> 20:20.636
OH, BOY.

20:20.719 --> 20:22.512
- DO YOU EVEN OWN A LEASH?
- IS IT TRUE?

20:22.596 --> 20:24.514
- WHEN EXACTLY DID YOU START
HATING SAN FRANCISCO?

20:24.598 --> 20:25.557
- NO, NO, NO.

20:25.641 --> 20:28.644
OKAY, WELL, YES.

20:28.727 --> 20:29.686
I WALKED HAPPY OFF LEASH!

20:29.770 --> 20:31.855
[people booing]

20:31.939 --> 20:33.523
I SWEAR IT WAS JUST
THAT ONE TIME.

20:33.607 --> 20:34.149
AND ANOTHER TIME.

20:34.232 --> 20:35.651
AND SOMETIMES MONDAYS.

20:35.734 --> 20:37.778
[toys squeaking]

20:37.861 --> 20:39.529
- FOUR MORE YEARS!
FOUR MORE YEARS!

20:39.613 --> 20:42.032
[laughs]

20:42.115 --> 20:45.744
- HUH?
[barking frantically]

20:51.917 --> 20:53.710
- HAPPY!

20:53.794 --> 20:55.337
HOW DID HAL EVEN GET
THOSE PHOTOS?

20:58.799 --> 21:00.550
PLEASE, IF I MAY.

21:00.634 --> 21:01.843
WHOA!

21:01.927 --> 21:03.470
OVER MY LONG WEEK
IN POLITICS,

21:03.553 --> 21:04.596
I'VE ALWAYS INSISTED

21:04.680 --> 21:08.141
THAT PET OWNERS TAKE
RESPONSIBILITY FOR THEIR PETS.

21:08.225 --> 21:11.311
FOR THIS REASON,
I'M DROPPING OUT OF THE RACE

21:11.395 --> 21:13.397
TO SPEND MORE TIME WITH MY DOG.

21:13.480 --> 21:14.398
- HUH?

21:14.481 --> 21:15.524
[people gasp]

21:15.607 --> 21:17.192
I HUMBLY THANK YOU ALL

21:17.275 --> 21:20.153
FOR ALMOST ALLOWING ME
THE PROFOUND HONOR

21:20.237 --> 21:21.822
OF BEING YOUR DOGCATCHER.

21:24.157 --> 21:26.910
I ONLY WANTED
TO CHANGE THE WORLD.

21:26.994 --> 21:30.038
BUT IN THE END...

21:30.122 --> 21:33.166
I GUESS I JUST FLEW
A LITTLE TOO CLOSE TO THE SUN.

21:36.044 --> 21:39.131
[applause]

21:44.094 --> 21:46.805
DON'T CRY FOR ME,
SAN FRANCISCO!

21:46.888 --> 21:49.474
THE TRUTH IS,
I'LL NEVER LEAVE YOU.

21:49.558 --> 21:53.895
- [speaks sadly]

21:53.979 --> 21:56.314
- WHAT?
YOU GAVE HAL THE PHOTOS?

21:56.398 --> 21:57.232
OH, HAPPY.

21:57.315 --> 22:00.068
- [whining]

22:00.152 --> 22:02.112
- LISTEN, IT'S OKAY.

22:02.195 --> 22:05.282
I WON THE CONTEST
THAT REALLY MATTERS.

22:05.365 --> 22:07.492
- [speaks inquiringly]

22:07.576 --> 22:10.871
- NO, NOT YOUR LOVE AND RESPECT;
THAT'S A GIVEN.

22:10.954 --> 22:12.581
I'M TALKING ABOUT
MY DEMOCRACY BADGE.

22:12.664 --> 22:14.291
- HUH?

22:14.374 --> 22:15.459
- YOU JUST HELPED ME CHECK OFF
MY LAST TWO TO-DOS:

22:15.542 --> 22:18.378
"FACE PUBLIC SCANDAL"
AND "RESIGN FROM OFFICE,

22:18.462 --> 22:21.381
CLAIMING TO WANT TO SPEND
MORE TIME WITH FAMILY."

22:24.009 --> 22:25.552
I MEAN, POLITICS ARE FINE,

22:25.635 --> 22:31.058
BUT I WANT TO CHANGE THE WORLD
THROUGH CAPITALISM AND GLITTER!

22:32.309 --> 22:35.979
